#Incompressible shear jet parameters

#Perturbation parameters.
#   yt:   Scales the thickness of the two shear layers. 0=infinitely thin
#   delx: Scales the amplitude of the vertical velocity perturbation. 0=no perturbation.
#TODO: Shouldn't the type be double?  How does MAESTRO make sure I keep all of the precision
#of my given default values?
yt                                  real             1.0d0/30.0d0
delx                                real             0.05d0

#Base state initial values
rho_base                            real             1.0d0
p_base                              real             1.0d0
